![high](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/high-priority.svg)

If the unique name retry budget is exhausted, `viewModel.duplicate` will throw an uncaught `SQLiteConstraintException`. Since this is launched in a coroutine scope from the UI without any exception handling, it will result in an application crash. Catching the exception and showing a Toast or error message to the user provides a much more robust and graceful user experience.

```kotlin
                    onDuplicate = {
                        scope.launch {
                            val duplicateName = context.getString(
                                R.string.keyboard_layouts_duplicate_name,
                                itemName,
                            )
                            try {
                                onNavigateToEditor(viewModel.duplicate(item.id, duplicateName))
                            } catch (e: android.database.sqlite.SQLiteConstraintException) {
                                android.widget.Toast.makeText(
                                    context,
                                    R.string.keyboard_layouts_name_taken,
                                    android.widget.Toast.LENGTH_SHORT
                                ).show()
                            }
                        }
                    },
```

![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

The retry loop can be simplified by using Kotlin's idiomatic `repeat` block. By running `repeat(CREATE_UNIQUE_NAME_MAX_ATTEMPTS - 1)` and attempting the final insertion outside the block, we can completely avoid the mutable `attempts` counter and the `while (true)` loop. If the final attempt fails, the `SQLiteConstraintException` will naturally propagate up.

```kotlin
        repeat(CREATE_UNIQUE_NAME_MAX_ATTEMPTS - 1) {
            try {
                return repository.create(uniqueName(base), spec)
            } catch (_: SQLiteConstraintException) {
                // Name taken since the check; recompute against current rows.
            }
        }
        return repository.create(uniqueName(base), spec)
```

